### From https://medium.com/@shouke.wei/python-libraries-for-robot-simulation-ffc5685b7209

1. PyBullet
   -a. Purpose: Physics-based robot simulation and reinforcement learning environment.
   -b. Key Features:
       -1. Realistic physics simulation (collisions, rigid body dynamics).
       -2. Support for URDF/SDF robot models.
       -3. Integrated with OpenAI Gym for RL experiments.

2. ROS + Gazebo (via Python APIs)
   -a. Purpose: Robot Operating System (ROS) integrates with Gazebo for full-featured 3D simulation.
   -b. Key Features:
       -1. Full robotics stack integration (sensors, control, navigation).  
       -2. High-fidelity physics and sensor simulation.
       -3. Python APIs (rospy) to control robots, run nodes, and process sensor data.
   -c. Use Cases: Autonomous vehicles, robotic arms, multi-robot systems.

3. V-REP / CoppeliaSim (Python Remote API)
   -a. Purpose: Industrial and research robot simulation platform with Python bindings.
   -b. Key Features:
       -1. Multi-robot coordination and path planning.
       -2. Real-time simulation and control.
       -3. Sensor and vision simulation.
   -c. Use Cases: Robotic manipulation, swarm robotics, mobile robots.

4. Webots
   -a. Purpose: Open-source mobile robot simulation platform with Python support.
   -b. Key Features:
       -1. High-quality 3D robot models.
       -2. Built-in controllers using Python.
       -3. Easy export of simulation data for analysis.
   -c. Use Cases: Autonomous navigation, robot learning, multi-robot experiments.

5. RoboPy / Klampt
   -a. Klampt: Kinematics, dynamics, and motion planning library in Python.
   -b. Purpose: Focus on planning, control, and physical simulation.
   -c. Features:
       -1. Robot kinematics/dynamics computations.
       -2. Collision detection.
       -3. Integrates with physics engines for motion simulation.

6. Gym and Reinforcement Learning Simulators
   -a. OpenAI Gym Robotics:
       -1. Python-friendly simulation environments for robotic tasks.
       -2. Tasks include arm manipulation, peg insertion, pushing, and more.
   -b. Features:
       -1. Integrates with PyBullet, MuJoCo, or other physics engines.
       -2. Used for testing RL algorithms on simulated robots.

